SIMPLE: rendition
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Rendition
<hw>Ren*di"tion</hw> <pr>(r?n-d?sh"?n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>rendere</ets> to render: cf. L. <ets>redditio</ets>. See
<er>Render</er>, and cf. <er>Reddition</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of rendering; especially, the act of
surrender, as of fugitives from justice, at the claim of a foreign
government; also, surrender in war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The rest of these brave men that suffered in cold blood after
articles of <qex>rendition</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Evelyn.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Translation; rendering; version.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>rendition</qex> of the word seems also most naturally to
agree with the genuine meaning of some other words in the same
verse.</q> <rj><qau>South.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Rendrock</ent>⟦br⟧
